  "body": "Hi there,\r\n\r\n#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `1.8.17-stable`\r\nOS & Version: Ubuntu 18\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nNeed to make watch only wallet\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nI have a system where users can generate addresses and recieve ETH. So every user need to have separate address. So I need to integrate HD wallet (watch-only) where users can gerneate addresses, where I can check transactions and balances. \r\nSo I have used `ethereumjs-wallet` to generate wallet and took from there `xpriv` key and I have tried to import into `geth`  which stored in my local machine (cold-storage)\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n```\r\nconst hdkey = require('ethereumjs-wallet/hdkey');\r\nconst bip39 = require('bip39');\r\nvar seed = bip39.mnemonicToSeed('my_mnemonic_phrase', 'my_password');\r\nvar chain = hdkey.fromMasterSeed(seed);\r\nvar xPrivate = chain.privateExtendedKey();\r\n```\r\nI have created file `file_to_path.txt` which contains my `xpriv` key.\r\n\r\nThan I have tried to import into `geth` by the command\r\n\r\n`geth account import file_to_path.txt`\r\n\r\n#### Backtrace\r\n\r\n````\r\nWARN [10-22|14:53:16.486] Sanitizing cache to Go's GC limits       provided=1024 updated=664\r\nFatal: Failed to load the private key: encoding/hex: invalid byte: U+0078 'x'\r\n\r\n````\r\n",
